            "description": "## Description\n\nThis ticket defines the scope for implementing **end-to-end observability** across the UCook platform using Datadog during the trial period.\n\nThe goal is to gain full visibility into system performance and reliability across all layers:\n\n* Infrastructure (hosts and Docker containers)\n* Backend services (API, Admin, PWA) via APM\n* Frontend (PWA) via RUM\n* Database (Postgres)\n* Cache & queue system (Redis + Bull)\n\nThe implementation should enable us to trace requests across the entire stack:\n\n**Browser → SSR → API → Database / Redis**\n\nand provide actionable insights into:\n\n* Performance bottlenecks\n* Error rates and failures\n* System health and resource usage\n* Queue backlogs and processing health\n\n---\n\n## Objectives\n\n* Establish real-time visibility into system health\n* Enable end-to-end request tracing across services\n* Detect and alert on performance degradation and failures\n* Provide dashboards for quick diagnosis of issues\n* Instrument queue and background job processing\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\nAt the end of the trial, we should be able to:\n\n* Trace a user request from frontend to backend and database\n* Identify the source of latency (frontend, SSR, API, DB, or queue)\n* Detect and respond to incidents via alerts\n* Monitor queue health and backlog trends\n* Use dashboards to understand system state without deep investigation\n\n---\n\n‌",
