            "description": "**Summary**\\\\nWhen a user creates a new address and attempts to set it as their default address, an unhandled rejection error is thrown: `Cannot read properties undefined`. The address is eventually set as default, but the process is unreliable and the error is surfaced to the user.\\\\n\\\\n  \n  \n**Steps to Reproduce**\\\\n1. Navigate to the user profile → Address tab\\\\n2. Add a new address\\\\n3. Attempt to set the newly created address as the default\\\\n\\\\n  \n  \n**Expected Behaviour**\\\\nThe address is set as default immediately and silently, with no errors.\\\\n\\\\n  \n  \n**Actual Behaviour**\\\\nAn error message appears: `Cannot read properties undefined`. The address may eventually be set as default, but the flow is broken and the unhandled rejection is logged in the console.\\\\n\\\\n  \n  \n**Notes**\\\\nIdentified during Admin Portal UAT session on 9 April 2026. The back-to-user-profile button on the address tab was previously fixed and is working correctly.",
