            "description": "**Identified in:** Admin Upgrade Testing session (30 Mar 2026)\n\n**Description**\n\nWhen attempting to download reports in the Operations section (under dispatch days), both on-demand and subscription order reports fail with an \"EA access error\" — \"not able to download the reports.\" This is a critical blocker for day-to-day operations.\n\n**Impact**\n\n* Cannot verify special box types (weekend/festive boxes with specific dispatch days)\n* Blocks preparation of stickers and boxing setups\n* Colleague Mishek relies on the order list download for preparing stickers and boxing setups\n* Cannot download full subscription order report (expected Excel sheet with all items: meal kits, wines, market items)\n\n**Steps to reproduce**\n\n1. Navigate to the Operations section\n2. Go to dispatch days and run the report generation process\n3. Attempt to download the Shipment details or subscription detail report\n4. \"EA access error\" is returned — download fails\n\n**Expected:** Reports download successfully as Excel files\n\n**Actual:** EA access error blocks download for both on-demand and subscription reports\n\n**Note:** A 15-minute re-test session with Denzel UCOOK and Mishek should be scheduled once this is resolved, before go-live.",
            "url": "https://silvertree-holdings-dev.atlassian.net/browse/UC-2839",
            "project": "UC"
