            "description": "**Summary**\\\\nWhen filtering wine-related items, not all vineyards are appearing in the filter dropdown. Additionally, it is not possible to select multiple farms simultaneously in the filter menu.\\\\n\\\\n**Steps to Reproduce**\\\\n1. Navigate to the wine products section of the Admin portal\\\\n2. Open the filter menu and look for vineyard/farm filters\\\\n3. Search for \"Struntfelt\" in the filter dropdown\\\\n4. Attempt to select both \"Struntfelt\" and \"Boschandal\" simultaneously in the filter\\\\n\\\\n**Expected Behaviour**\\\\n- All vineyards/farms should appear in the filter dropdown\\\\n- Multiple farms should be selectable simultaneously to allow combined filtering\\\\n\\\\n**Actual Behaviour**\\\\n- \"Struntfelt\" and other vineyards are missing from the filter dropdown\\\\n- Users can search for an individual vineyard by name in the general search box, but cannot select multiple farms in the filter menu at the same time\\\\n\\\\n**Context**\\\\nReported by Lauren Nel during Admin Upgrade internal testing session (2026-03-25). Anand Sharma confirmed they would investigate why not all vineyards appear in filters, and whether a search function could be added to the filter menu.",
